title: Arsenal vs Bayern Munich: Arsene Wenger makes two changes for Champions League tie | Metro News
text:
Sean Kearns for Metro.co.uk Wednesday 15 Feb 2017 6:42 pm Arsenal are aiming to make the quarter finals for the first time since 2010 (Picture: Getty) 
Theo Walcott has been dropped from Arsenal’s starting XI for the Gunners’ Champions League first leg clash with Bayern Munich at the Allianz Arena. 
The England forward has made way for Granit Xhaka, with Alexis Sanchez keeping his spot up top. Paul Pogba shows brotherly love after Florentin is forced off injured 
Arsene Wenger’s side have a dismal record in the last-16 of the competition and are looking to make the quarter finals for the first time since 2010. 
Elsewhere, the Frenchman’s stuck true to his word by picking David Ospina over Petr Cech, while Alex Oxlade-Chamberlain is expected to take a wide position in midfield. Here we go… this is how we’ll line up for #FCBvAFC pic.twitter.com/XcCJ7h9nBN 
— Arsenal FC (@Arsenal) February 15, 2017 
Ancelotti is without Jerome Boateng and Franck Ribery for tonight’s clash and has opted for Javi Martinez and Douglas Costa instead. #FCBayern XI: Neuer – Lahm, Hummels, Martínez, Alaba – Xabi Alonso, Vidal – Robben, Thiago, Costa – Lewandowski. #UCL #FCBARS
